org.apache.ambari.server.state.kerberos

Class KerberosServiceDescriptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ambari.server.state.kerberos.AbstractKerberosDescriptor
      • org.apache.ambari.server.state.kerberos.AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer
        • org.apache.ambari.server.state.kerberos.KerberosServiceDescriptor

  • public class KerberosServiceDescriptor
extends AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer
    KerberosServiceDescriptor is an implementation of an AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer that encapsulates an Ambari service and it components.

    A KerberosServiceDescriptor has the following properties:

    • name
    • components
    • identities (AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer)
    • configurations (AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer)

    The following (pseudo) JSON Schema will yield a valid KerberosServiceDescriptor 

       {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#",
      "title": "KerberosServiceDescriptor",
      "description": "Describes an Ambari service",
      "type": "object",
      "preconfigure": "boolean",
      "properties": {
        "name": {
          "description": "An identifying name for this service descriptor.",
          "type": "string"
        },
        "components": {
          "description": "A list of Ambari component descriptors",
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "title": "KerberosComponentDescriptor"
            "type": "KerberosComponentDescriptor"
          }
        },
        "identities": {
          "description": "A list of Kerberos identity descriptors",
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "title": "KerberosIdentityDescriptor"
            "type": "KerberosIdentityDescriptor"
          }
        },
        "configurations": {
          "description": "A list of relevant configuration blocks",
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "title": "KerberosConfigurationDescriptor"
            "type": "KerberosConfigurationDescriptor"
          }
        }
      }
   }

    In this implementation, AbstractKerberosDescriptor.name will hold the KerberosServiceDescriptor#name value.
